# Responsive Layout Triage: Legacy vs New Site

**Date:** 2026-05-25
**Source:** https://dzackgarza.com/advice%20and%20resources/some-topics-to-learn-for-graduate-school-in-mathematics/
**Target:** New Pandoc + Svelte site

## Legacy Breakpoint Architecture

Minimal Mistakes theme 4.21.0 uses these breakpoints:

| Label | Width | `html font-size` | Layout |
|-------|-------|-------------------|--------|
| Base | <600px | 16px | Single column, stacked |
| `min-width: 37.5em` | ≥600px | 16px | 2-col grid for related posts |
| `min-width: 48em` | ≥768px | 12px | 4-col grid, larger screens |
| `min-width: 64em` | ≥1024px | 14px | **3-column**: sidebar + content + TOC |
| `min-width: 80em` | ≥1280px | 16px | Scale up: sidebar/TOC 200px→300px, #main locks to 1280px |

---

## Feature Gap Table

Each row is a legacy feature. Current state: ✅ present, ⚠️ partial, ❌ missing.

| # | Feature | Status | Details |
|---|---------|--------|---------|
| 1 | **Responsive font-size scaling** | ❌ | Legacy: `html { font-size }` changes: 16→12→14→16px across breakpoints, resizing ALL typography. New: fixed Tailwind scale at all sizes. |
| 2 | **Greedy nav (hamburger overflow)** | ❌ | Legacy: `.greedy-nav` JS calculates available width vs link widths. Overflow links move to `.hidden-links` dropdown. Button count: <768px = 0, <1024px = 1, <1280px = 2, else = 3. New: `flex-wrap` — links wrap to multiple lines. |
| 3 | **Search overlay (Lunr.js)** | ❌ | Legacy: Full-text client-side search via Lunr. Search overlay toggled by `.search__toggle`. Index built from posts. New: No search. |
| 4 | **Disqus comments** | ❌ | Legacy: Disqus thread on each post. New: None. |
| 5 | **Social sharing buttons** | ❌ | Legacy: Share buttons (Twitter, Facebook, LinkedIn, etc.) on posts. New: None. |
| 6 | **Image lightbox (Magnific Popup)** | ❌ | Legacy: Click post images → lightbox popup. New: No lightbox. |
| 7 | **Post taxonomy display** | ⚠️ | Legacy: Tags AND categories listed separately with icons (`.page__taxonomy`). New: Tags only (`.post-tags`). No categories. |
| 8 | **Left sidebar (author card)** | ⚠️ | Legacy: At ≥1024px, left sidebar with avatar, name, bio, social links. Sticky. Collapses to inline below. New: Profile card always visible at ≥768px (md breakpoint, not 1024px). Sticky not applied to profile card. Missing some social links. |
| 9 | **Right TOC sidebar** | ⚠️ | Legacy: At ≥1024px, TOC in right sidebar, absolutely positioned, sticky. Below: inline at top of content. New: `.post-sidebar` at ≥1024px via `grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr`. Sticky. Close match but breakpoint uses legacy's 1024px, not Tailwind's 768px `md:`. Need to verify TOC renders at all. |
| 10 | **Related posts grid** | ⚠️ | Legacy: 1-col (<600px), 2-col (600–767px), 4-col (≥768px). Uses float with exact legacy percentages. New: 2-col (<1024px), 4-col (≥1024px). Missing the 600px breakpoint for 1-col→2-col transition. |
| 11 | **Post metadata (read time)** | ⚠️ | Legacy: Shows read time with clock icon. New: `.page__meta-readtime` exists in post-navigation filter for related cards. Main blog listing read time — need to verify. |
| 12 | **Post pagination (prev/next)** | ⚠️ | Legacy: Full-width pagination bars with Previous/Next labels. `.pagination` class. New: Implemented in Lua filter, matches class names. Need to verify visual fidelity. |
| 13 | **URL path prefix (BASE_URL)** | ⚠️ | Legacy: Absolute paths starting with `/`. New: `//blog/...` (double slash) or `/website/...` depending on compile context. Works with `just build` but breaks in dev mode. |
| 14 | **Sticky sidebar behavior** | ⚠️ | Legacy: Left sidebar sticky at ≥1024px via `.sidebar.sticky`. Right TOC sticky at ≥1024px via `.sidebar__right.sticky`. New: Post-sidebar has sticky. Left profile card does NOT have sticky. |
| 15 | **Max-width container** | ⚠️ | Legacy: `#main { max-width: 1280px }` at ≥80em, else 100%. New: `max-w-6xl` (1152px) at all sizes via Tailwind. Different value, no breakpoint. |
| 16 | **Footer** | ⚠️ | Legacy: Multiple sections: Follow links, copyright, MathJax config, Disqus. New: Single line `$site.profile.name$`. Minimal. |
| 17 | **MathJax for LaTeX** | ❌ | Legacy: MathJax CDN for rendering `$...$` and `$$...$$`. New: Not loaded. Pandoc may use MathJax in compilation but client-side rendering not configured. |
| 18 | **Skip links / a11y** | ⚠️ | Legacy: `<nav class="skip-links">` with Skip to primary navigation/content/footer. New: No skip links. `aria-label` attributes present on nav elements. |
| 19 | **Breadcrumbs** | ❌ | Legacy: Not on this page, but present in theme and on some pages. New: Not present. |

---

## Responsive Layout Comparison: Mobile (<600px)

| Element | Legacy | New |
|---------|--------|-----|
| Sidebar | `clear: both` — full-width block above content. Author avatar inline (table-cell), small. | Grid collapses at <768px (Tailwind `md:`). Below: profile card stacks above content as full-width block. |
| TOC | Inline `<aside>` inside `section.page__content`, before body text. | `post-sidebar` has `display: none` below 1024px. No inline TOC below breakpoint. |
| Navigation | Greedy nav: hamburger icon, hidden links dropdown. Site title + toggle visible. | `flex-wrap`: all links visible, wraps to multiple lines. |
| Related posts | 1-column, stacked full-width. | 2-column float layout. Grid items at 48.9% width. |
| Container | `max-width: 100%`, padding 1em. | `w-full` + px-5 (1.25rem). |

## Responsive Layout Comparison: Desktop (≥1024px)

| Element | Legacy | New |
|---------|--------|-----|
| Left sidebar | Float left, `calc(200px - 1em)` wide. Sticky. | Grid column `16rem` (256px) — wider than legacy 200px. No sticky. |
| Right TOC | Absolute position, 200px wide, `margin-right: -200px`. Sticky. | Grid column `1fr` in `2fr 1fr` grid. Sticky. |
| Page content | `float: right; width: calc(100% - 200px); padding-right: 200px`. | Grid auto width. |
| Post nav / related | `float: right; width: calc(100% - 200px)`. | Full width. |
| Font size | `html { font-size: 14px }` → scaled down. | Fixed Tailwind sizes. |

---

## Triage Priority Levels

- **P0 (Must fix)** — Bugs / missing content that breaks the user experience
- **P1 (Layout parity)** — Visual/structural differences from legacy that are immediately noticeable
- **P2 (Feature parity)** — Missing features that users expect
- **P3 (Polish)** — Nice-to-have improvements

### P0 — Defects

| Ref | Issue | Current behavior | Expected |
|-----|-------|-----------------|----------|
| P0-1 | Trailing-slash 404 on blog posts | `/blog/topics-for-grad-school/` renders `<NotFound>`. Route match via strict `===` with manifest route (no trailing slash). | Either strip trailing slash via redirect, or generate both variants in manifest. |
| P0-2 | BASE_URL missing from compiled output in dev mode | `//blog/...` and `//assets/...` instead of `/website/...` | Use consistent path resolution irrespective of compile context. |
| P0-3 | Broken image assets | `public/assets/images/*.png` are Git LFS pointers (ASCII text) until `git lfs pull`. Served as `image/png`, browser loads but `naturalWidth=0`. | Real image content must be present after checkout. LFS smudge must work. |

### P1 — Layout Parity

| Ref | Issue | Effort | Notes |
|-----|-------|--------|-------|
| P1-1 | Font-size responsive scaling | 1 day | Add `html { font-size }` changes at breakpoints matching legacy. Adjusts ALL typography proportionally. Conflicts with Tailwind's fixed-size approach. May need custom CSS overrides. |
| P1-2 | Greedy nav (hamburger overflow) | 1–2 days | Port or reimplement greedy nav JS. Calculate link widths vs container. Move overflow to dropdown. Adjust visible count at each breakpoint (768:0, 1024:1, 1280:2, else:3). |
| P1-3 | Inline TOC below 1024px | 0.5 day | Change `post-sidebar` from `display: none` to inline block below breakpoint. TOC appears at top of content, matching legacy position before body text. |
| P1-4 | Left sidebar sticky | 0.5 day | Add `position: sticky; top: 2rem` to `.academic-profile-card` at ≥1024px. |
| P1-5 | Related posts grid breakpoints | 0.5 day | Add `@media (min-width: 37.5em)` / 600px breakpoint for 1-col→2-col transition. Currently 2-col at all sizes below 1024px. |
| P1-6 | Container max-width | 0.25 day | Change `max-w-6xl` to match legacy 1280px at ≥80em breakpoint. |

### P2 — Feature Parity

| Ref | Issue | Effort | Notes |
|-----|-------|--------|-------|
| P2-1 | Client-side search (Lunr.js) | 3–5 days | Index generation from compiled posts, Lunr library, search overlay UI. Significant feature. |
| P2-2 | Disqus comments | 0.5 day | Add Disqus embed script to post template. Requires Disqus shortname config. |
| P2-3 | Social sharing buttons | 0.5 day | Add share links (Twitter, Facebook, email, etc.) with appropriate URLs. |
| P2-4 | Image lightbox | 1 day | Implement or integrate lightbox (Magnific Popup or simpler). Click on images in post content. |
| P2-5 | MathJax integration | 0.5 day | Load MathJax CDN script for LaTeX rendering. Pandoc compiles with `html-math-method: mathjax`. |
| P2-6 | Category display | 0.25 day | Add categories to post metadata display alongside tags. |
| P2-7 | Breadcrumbs | 1 day | Add breadcrumb navigation, especially for category/taxonomy pages. |

### P3 — Polish

| Ref | Issue | Effort | Notes |
|-----|-------|--------|-------|
| P3-1 | Footer expansion | 0.5 day | Add social links, copyright, additional sections matching legacy footer. |
| P3-2 | Skip links / a11y | 0.25 day | Add skip navigation links at top of page. |
| P3-3 | Post read-time icon | 0.25 day | Add clock icon next to read time (legacy uses Font Awesome `fa-clock`). |

---

## Implementation Strategy

**Phase 1 (P0 fixes):** Fix the three defects that make the site unusable or inconsistent regardless of layout.

1. P0-1: Trailing-slash redirect (React Router or nginx)
2. P0-2: BASE_URL path consistency
3. P0-3: LFS setup documented + asset integrity test in CI

**Phase 2 (P1 layout parity):** Bring responsive layout and viewport behavior to match legacy site. This is the meat of the user's complaint — the site should respond differently at each breakpoint, not just have a single column layout at all sizes with a grid breakpoint at 1024px.

4. P1-1: Responsive font-size scaling
5. P1-2: Greedy nav overflow menu
6. P1-3: Inline TOC below 1024px
7. P1-4: Left sidebar sticky
8. P1-5: Related posts grid breakpoint fix
9. P1-6: Max-width lock at 1280px

**Phase 3 (P2 feature parity):** Add missing features.

10. P2-1 through P2-7

**Phase 4 (P3 polish):** Final visual alignment.

11. P3-1 through P3-3

---

## Verification

Each phase must include:
- Playwright visual regression test against the deployed build at `http://localhost/website/`
- Manual visual inspection at each breakpoint: <600px, 600–767px, 768–1023px, 1024–1279px, ≥1280px
- Comparison screenshot against legacy site at matching breakpoints
